  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large ceramic tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper, and ground ginger. Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the chicken broth and bring to a boil.",
    "Add the white sauerkraut and return to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, or until the sauerkraut is tender and the flavors have melded together.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Stir in chopped parsley and serve over rice or with pita bread.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
